                                    <h2>Summary</h2>
                                    <!-- My testimonial here -->
                                        <p>This project marked my entry into professional software development, where I architected and implemented the complete backend infrastructure for Arkansas state government. The engagement established a long-term relationship that continues today through ongoing contract work for feature development.</p>

                                        <p>The core deliverable was a comprehensive CMS enabling legislative staff to manage all website content independently. I implemented the <a target="_blank" href="https://csv.thephpleague.com/">League CSV</a> package to provide instant data export capabilities, allowing administrators to generate spreadsheet reports of currently elected representatives on demand.</p>

                                        <p>My responsibilities focused on backend architecture—designing the database schema, implementing RESTful routing and controllers, and connecting data models to frontend views. I also delivered mobile-responsive enhancements to the "Find My Representative" mapping tool powered by Google Maps API.</p>

                                        <p>The client continues to contract with me for ongoing feature development. A recent example is the <a href="https://www.arkansashouse.org/news/33046/download-news-letter-as-pdf" target="_blank">on-demand PDF generation system</a>, which allows representatives to distribute their news posts as professionally formatted PDF newsletters to constituents.</p>
                                    
